                        </tr>

                        <tr>
                            <td class="required">Scheme</td>
                            <td>Migration scheme to use</td>
                        </tr>

                        <tr>
                            <td>Quiesce</td>
                            <td>CSD-based CICS Configurations only: specifies whether to set each resource to a (resource-type-dependent) status that allows its definition to be installed (for example, disabled, closed, or out of service), before attempting to install to it. If you do not specify this "quiesce" option, and a resource is in a status that does not allow the install action, then the install action for that resource definition will fail</td>
                        </tr>

                        <tr>
                            <td class="required">Qualification Data</td>
                            <td>Qualification Data is optional data passed through the Install operations qualification exit point. The needs of your organization determine whether you use an exit program and what processing it performs</td>
                        </tr>

                        <tr>
                            <td>Discard</td>
                            <td>Whether to discard the resource definition before attempting to install it</td>
                        </tr>

                        <tr>
                            <td>Force</td>
                            <td>Applies only to Context-based CICS configurations</td>
                        </tr>

                        <tr>
                            <td>Target Scope</td>
                            <td>Required for Context-based CICS configurations, ommit for CDS-based CICS configurations</td>
                        </tr>

                        <tr>
                            <td>Resource Group Object Type</td>
                            <td>Filter to select resource definitions of a particular type, excluding any other types of resource definition in the ResGroup, applies only to Context-based CICS configurations</td>
                        </tr>

                        <tr>
